Dependencies
============
* python-augeas
* python-sphinx


Modules
-------
* Mysql
  apt-get install python-mysqldb

Client
------
* python-prettytable
* pip install argcomplete

Install All dependencies
------------------------
apt-get install python-augeas python-sphinx python-prettytable python-mysqldb
pip install argcomplete


Test Lifecycle and Augeas
=========================
cd mss/agent/classes/mss3
export PYTHONPATH=$PWD
mkdir /tmp/etc
cp -r /etc/mysql /tmp/etc/


Non interactive test
---------------------
python tests/tests_lifecycle.py

Interactive tests
-----------------
./client.py --help

To add client completion, run
eval "$(~/.local/bin/register-python-argcomplete  client.py)"

To get module documentation
---------------------------
python client-xmlrpc.py load Mysql
python client-xmlrpc.py dot Mysql > mysql.dot
dotty mysql.dot


To get full documentation
-------------------------
cd doc/
make html
firefox build/html/index.html


Ideas
=====
* Specify stability of states: unstable, exp, stable ...
  In order to manage community modules